## Agenda setting for LA wildfires recovery: A closer look at the comments 

The agenda-setting phase of the Los Angeles wildfires recovery engagement is complete. We're now using the comments we got in that phase to shape talks that will help us solve important problems. You can download the comments to see what people said yourself.

----
id: plots_interpretation
----

## How to interpret these charts

Each scatterplot represents the comments for one of the key tensions outlined in the findings report that summarizes Engaged California’s work so far on Los Angeles wildfires recovery. 

These charts show how opinions and priorities vary related to each key tension. This shows why these key tensions will make good deliberation topics

1. because there is clearly a difference of opinion & strong beliefs and priorities, and 
2. there is some consensus to dig into deeper (aka the clusters).

Each dot represents an individual comment. Comments that are identified by an LLM model as  semantically similar to each other are mapped closer to each other. 

Each comment is also labelled with a subcategory. We also used an AI model to define subcategories for each key tension. Each subcategory is defined by a color in the visual (with grey dots representing comments that are related to the key tension, but did not map cleanly to one of the subcategories).

